Quote Approval Patterns Checklist

Data Requirements
- Fields needed:
  - Customer name, contact info
  - Quote ID
  - Items/services, quantity, pricing
  - Approval status (pending, approved, rejected)

Validation rules
- Quote amount must be numeric
- Approval status must be restricted to defined values

Security Checklist
- Role‑based access:
  - Only authorized staff can approve or rejected
- Audit trail:
  - Log approver name, role, timestamp
- Data retention:
  - Quotes stored for minimum 5 years (compliance)
- Sensitive data:
  - Customer personal info not exposed in logs

After Approval
- Quote converted into invoice or sent to customer
- Approval logged in audit trail
- Notifications sent to relevant team members

After Rejection
- Quote flagged as rejected in system
- Editable and resubmittable after adjustments
- Rejection must be logged

Integration Notes
- External systems:
  - QuickBooks / Xero APIs for quote handling
- Endpoints needed:
  - Submit new quote
  - Update approval status
  - Fetch approval history
- Notifications:
  - Email or dashboard alerts on approval/rejection

Example Scenarios
- Example 1: Quote under R10,000 → auto‑approval or single manager approval
- Example 2: Quote above R50,000 → manager + finance approval required
- Example 3: Quote rejected at R20,000 → editable, resubmittable, logged in audit trail
